===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|其|月|t2=moon|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}} – changing moon marks the passage of time, hence a period of time. In the original version, there was a sun 日 instead of the moon, hence the original version is 㫷 (with variant 𣇳). Then, the character became [[朞]].

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|其|id=1|should; probably}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

